<p>I'm trying to figure out this doozie: 01 1011 - 11 1101 </p>  <p>use 2's complement to solve, 6bits signed.</p>  <p>This is what I tried:</p>  <p>range of 6bits: -32 to 31</p>  <p>01 1011 = 27</p>  <p>11 1101 = -29</p>  <p>27 -(-29) = 56 (overflow)</p>  <p>11 1101 -- 2s complement --> 10 0011</p>  <p>so </p>  <p>01 1011 + 10  0011 = (missing bit)11 1110 = -2!</p>  <p>Any luck?</p>